  content: `
<h1>What its magic lamp</h1><i>The Magic Lamp is one of the main tools in the game.</i><i>Through it, you collect gear that has different Affixes.</i><br><i>It has a total of 35 levels, to reach the next level, you need tо</i> <i>collect a certain amount of gold. You collect gold when you use the lamp and sell gear that you don't need.</i><br><h1>Gear tier and required level</h1><ul><li>Normal (Grey) ~ level 1</li><li>Unique (Green) ~ level 1</li><li>Well (Blue) ~ level 1</li><li>Rare (Purple) ~ level 2</li><li>Mythic (Yellow) ~ level 4</li><li>Epic (Orange) ~ level 7</li><li>Legendary (Red) ~ level 9</li><li>immortal (Pink) ~ level 13</li><li>Supreme (Rainbow) ~ level 20</li><li>Aurous (Gold) ~ level 24</li><li>Eternal (White) ~ level 28, Character level 125, 60 day of server relase</li></ul><img src="images/lamp5.jpg" class="post-img"><br><h1>Required gold for level of Magic Lamp</h1><br><img src="images/lamp6.jpg" class="post-img"><br><h1>Gear Affix</h1><br><i>Combo, Counterstrike, Stun, Evasion, Regeneration, Skill Crit, Pal Crit, Pal Combo</i><br><h1>Auto use</h1><i>Basically, the lamp is used by pressing it, but there is also an automatic use, which makes its use much easier and more pleasant.</i><br><br><i>Using this feature requires a character level of 16. To the right of the lamp there is an icon like a setting, labeled Auto. By clicking on it, a screen with the following functions will open:</i><br><ul><li><b>Quality</b> - From here you choose what tier of equipment you want to receive. You always receive the selected one and have the option to get a higher one. Equipment that is below this selection is sold automatically.</li><li><b>Filter 1 & Filter 2</b> -Here you choose what Affix gear should have, any gear that does not have an Affix of your choice is sold automatically, even if it is of the Quality you selected above.</li><li><b>Number of lamps used at onece = X</b> - From here you choose how many lamps to use at once. Every 4 levels the selection increases by 2, except at level 28, you can use 20 at once, before that the maximum is 10. <br> I personally always use the maximum unlocked option for the following reasons: you get XP faster, gold faster, there is a greater chance of getting what you need than if you open them 1 by 1.</li></ul><img src="images/lamp3.jpg" class="post-img"><br><br><div class="highlight" style="border-left:3px solid red">Personally, I would not recommend using filters on Auto Lamp before Supreme Gear. Because no matter how useful it is, it would delay the acquisition of higher class gear. Because if, for example, you have just unlocked a level 13 lamp and put a filter on, you will receive immortal equipment much more slowly, because the percentage of obtaining it is small, and with filters it becomes even smaller.</div><br><div class="highlight">But if you do decide to use them, the best approach I've found so far is this: Immortal gear has just been unlocked, and you're still on Legendary, use the Quality Legendary and above option, for filter - Archer for example: Filter 1 - Crit rate / Any & Filter 2 - Any / Combo. This way you're more likely to get what you want. Whenever you unlock a new gear quality, use the previous quality and above, from what I've seen, it's much easier to replace old gear with new, almost perfect affixes with this method.</div><br><br><h1>Filter Magic Lamp Atrributes</h1><ul><li>Morh - from here u can select skin for your lamp.</li><li>Adjust - Here you can select up to 3 filters, for example Combo, Crit rate, Counterstrike. Gear that has these attributes will automatically be sold. I personally use Pal combo & Pal crit, because I play Warrior, and gear with these attributes is not useful for me. The same goes for Archer and Mage.</li></ul><img src="images/lamp4.jpg" class="post-img">
  `,
